---
layout: layouts/project.njk
title: CSS3 Patterns
tagline: Drawing with CSS. Next Level.
preview: "/images/css-patterns.png"
---
{% set stylesheets %}
  {% include "../styles/css3-patterns/index.css" %}
{% endset %}

<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero__inner">
    <a id="link-to-homepage" href="/">eCSSpert.com</a>
    <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
    <h3>{{ tagline }}</h3>
  </div>
</div>

<p>What I've learned from <a href="/css3-logos/">CSS3 Logos</a> is that having fun is the key to succes. So, based on an idea by <a href="https://leaverou.github.io/css3patterns/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lea Verou</a>, I decided to make my own collection of CSS3 Patterns.</p>
<p>I hope you'll enjoy them as much as I loved figuring out the intricate puzzle behind each of them.</p>

<ul class="patterns">
  {%- for post in collections.css3patterns -%}
    <li id="{{ post.fileSlug }}" class="pattern">
      <div class="info">
        <h2>{{ post.data.title | safe }}</h2>
      </div>
      <a href="./{{ post.fileSlug }}/" class="showcase"></a>
    </li>
    {% set pattern %}
      .html { {{ post.data.pattern }} }
    {% endset %}
    {% set stylesheets %}
      {{ stylesheets | safe }} #{{ post.fileSlug }} .showcase { {{ post.data.pattern }} }
    {% endset %}
  {%- endfor -%}
</ul>
<style>
  {{ stylesheets | cssmin | safe }}
</style>